To generated the above code, I have enabled all possible optimizations through [compiler directives][1], meaning that the unwieldy C code generated by `a.size` cannot be optimized away. It looks to me as though the `size` &quot;attribute&quot; is not really a pre-computed attribute, but actually carries out a computation upon lookup. Furthermore, this computation is quite a bit more involved than simply taking the product over the `shape` attribute. I cannot find any hint of an explanation in the [docs][2].

What is the explanation of this behavior, and do I have a better choice than writing out `a.shape[0]*a.shape[1]*a.shape[2]`, if I really care about this micro optimization?


